wikipedia_page.main: Ivor Thomas Davies (6 April 1892 – 2 July 1959) was a Welsh international rugby union player who played club rugby predominantly for Llanelli. Davies earned three caps for Wales before his career was disrupted by the outbreak of the First World War, in which he served.
